<HEADLINE>
CAR SALES DOWN 28.8 PERCENT IN 2006
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei,  Jan.  3 (CNA) 01/03/07  18:05:01 (By Nick Huang)
</P>
<P>
Due to the credit card debt problem in Taiwan, car sales totalled
only 366,000 for 2006, down 28.8 percent from the figure of
514,000 for the previous year, according to statistics released
Wednesday by the Ministry of Transportation and Communications.
</P>
<P>
The ministry also forecast that car sales will reach between
360,000 and 380,000 for 2007.
</P>
<P>
The number of cars sold in the last month of 2006 amounted to
30,800, up 17.3 percent from November, according to the
ministry's tallies.
</P>
